document_data.Defenses:
[[File:Castle Waterdeep.jpg|thumb|right|''Castle Waterdeep at sunset.'']]
Its walls were 60-ft-thick (18 m) on average, and high enough that when banners were displayed in honor of visiting parties, they were visible from many areas of the southern city.

The road up to the castle's main entrance was steep-sided and winding, with towers guarding it at regular points.{{Cite comic/Lawyers!|7}}

document_data.History:
Work began on the castle in the [[963 DR|Year of the Thundering Horde, 963 DR]], outside and to the north of the city walls. It was finished on [[Higharvestide]], the [[974 DR|Year of the Haunting Harpy, 974 DR]], the same year [[Laroun]] rose to War Lord.

During the [[Time of Troubles]] of the [[1358 DR|Year of Shadows, 1358 DR]], a party was held at Castle Waterdeep in honor of a [[Shar|supposed avatar]] of the goddess [[Sel√ªne]]. It was attended by Lord [[Piergeiron]], [[Khelben Arunsun]], [[Tertius Wands]], [[Mirt]] and [[Asper]], and [[Fenn Estelmer]] and [[Kyriani]], who came to investigate the avatar. However, a trio of the [[Dark Army of the Night]] crashed the party and made a failed attempt to kidnap the avatar, before they were arrested by the [[City Guard (Waterdeep)|City Guard]]. Kyriani later confronted the avatar in the castle kitchens, but the two fought a [[spell]]-battle that spilled out into the corridor before Lord Piergeiron intervened. Khelben helped Kyriani escape with a ''[[passwall]]'' through the castle walls. Dramatically, she leaped out of the cliff-side castle and was caught by her lover [[Rellamyn]] on his [[asperii|flying horse]]. He and his companions swooped the castle, dodged flaming arrows from its defenders, before they departed.{{Cite comic/Dark of the Moon}}

As of [[1372 DR]], it had long since been inside the city walls.
